structure.unit: PHYSICIANS, OSTEOPATHS, PODIATRISTS, AND RELATED MEDICAL PRACTITIONERS

law.text: Every person licensed to practice podiatry shall, within thirty (30) days after issuance, file his license with the county clerk of each county in which he desires to engage in the practice of podiatry.
law.history: Amended 1974 Ky. Acts ch. 225, sec. 12. -- Amended 1962 Ky. Acts ch. 289, sec. 6. -- Created 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 176, sec. 7.
